edu.kit.informatik.matchthree.framework

Class Token

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.kit.informatik.matchthree.framework.Token
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Token>

    public final class Token
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Token>
    Represents a token on a game board.

    A token has a string representation that is exactly one character long. The string representation must not be a semicolon (;) or whitespace.

    Two tokens are equal if their string representation are equal.

    Tokens are compared via String.compareTo(String) on their string representations.

    The string representation can be obtained using toString().

    Author:
    IPD Koziolek

        public static java.util.stream.Stream<Token> stream(java.lang.String tokenString)
        Convenience method for creating a Stream of Tokens from a String. Each character of the String (as obtained by CharSequence.chars()) is one element in the returned Stream. Empty tokens (whitespace) are returned as a null value.
        Parameters:

        Returns:
